{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6a98d3c9-cc64-4d44-9cbc-b680da22f3dc","content":"In ASP.NET Core, `AddScoped` creates one instance **per HTTP request** — each request gets a fresh `DbContext`. But MAUI has no request pipeline. The app uses a **single DI scope for its entire lifetime**, so `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton`. Your `DbContext` is never disposed/recreated between navigations.\n\n**Fixes:**\n\n1. **Use `AddTransient`** — gives a new `DbContext` each time it's injected:\n   ```csharp\n   builder.Services.AddTransient<MyDbContext>();\n   ```\n\n2. **Use a DbContext factory** (preferred for more control):\n   ```csharp\n   builder.Services.AddDbContextFactory<MyDbContext>();\n   ```\n   Then inject `IDbContextFactory<MyDbContext>` and create short-lived contexts:\n   ```csharp\n   using var db = _factory.CreateDbContext();\n   ```\n\nThe factory approach mirrors the \"per-request\" pattern most closely and avoids issues with tracked entities leaking across operations.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"630baabe-4ef7-4ff7-bfb1-f055c3b19e1a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a common issue when using `AddScoped` with a `DbContext` in a .NET MAUI application. This is a well-known gotcha related to how dependency injection scopes work differently in MAUI compared to ASP.NET Core.\n\nIn ASP.NET Core, a \"scope\" is created per HTTP request, so `AddScoped` gives you a new instance per request. But in MAUI, there's no concept of an HTTP request — the DI container typically has a single scope for the entire application lifetime. This means `AddScoped` behaves essentially like `AddSingleton`, so your DbContext instance lives for the entire app lifetime, causing data to persist across navigations.\n\n\nThis is general knowledge about how MAUI's dependency injection works, so I don't need to dig into any specific codebase to explain it.","outputTokens":455,"requestId":"9421:301399:156425E:17DEBA8:6A06739F"},"id":"e5f3c2d3-396c-4b51-bd79-1d2d8e106053","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:15:22.836Z","parentId":"74b282f4-759b-4319-91ce-2edfcc4f5965"}
